-- Eni Is Seeking $6.2 Billion for Its 33% Galp Stake, Diario Economico Says
-- B y   J i m   S i l v e r
-- 2010-12-30T07:43:24Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-12-30/eni-is-seeking-6-2-billion-for-its-33-galp-stake-diario-economico-says.html
Eni SpA is asking 4.7 billion euros
($6.2 billion), or 17 euros a share, for its 33.34 percent stake
in Portuguese oil-and-gas company Galp Energia SGPS SA, Diario
Economico reported, without saying where it got the information.
A spokesman for the Italian company declined to comment on that
figure, the newspaper said.  Eni is discussing the sale of the stake to Petroleo
Brasileiro SA, Diario said.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Jim Silver at 
 jsilver@bloomberg.net  